# Privacy Policy for Nexura

**Effective Date:** [Insert Date]  
**Last Updated:** [Insert Date]

## 1. Introduction

Welcome to Nexura ("we," "our," or "us"). This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use our social media management platform and related services (collectively, the "Service").

By using our Service, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this Privacy Policy. If you do not agree with the terms of this Privacy Policy, please do not access or use the Service.

## 2. Information We Collect

### 2.1 Personal Information You Provide

**Account Information:**
- Name and email address
- Username and password
- Profile picture and bio
- Payment information (processed by third-party payment processors)
- Company or organization details

**Content and Communications:**
- Social media posts, images, videos, and other content you create
- Comments, messages, and communications within the platform
- Feedback, support requests, and correspondence with us

### 2.2 Social Media Account Information

When you connect your social media accounts to our Service, we collect:
- Account usernames and profile information
- Access tokens and authorization credentials
- Public posts and engagement metrics
- Follower/following information
- Account analytics and performance data

**Supported Platforms:**
- Facebook (including Instagram)
- Twitter/X
- LinkedIn
- TikTok
- YouTube
- Other platforms as added to our Service

### 2.3 Automatically Collected Information

**Usage Data:**
- Log files and server logs
- IP addresses and device information
- Browser type and version
- Operating system and device identifiers
- Time stamps and session duration
- Pages visited and features used
- Clickstream data and user interactions

**Cookies and Tracking Technologies:**
- Session cookies for functionality
- Persistent cookies for preferences
- Analytics cookies for performance monitoring
- Third-party cookies from integrated services

### 2.4 Information from Third Parties

**RSS Feeds and News Sources:**
- Content from subscribed RSS feeds
- News articles from Google News and other sources
- Publicly available content for curation purposes

**AI and Media Services:**
- Generated content from AI services
- Stock photos and media from integrated providers
- Analytics data from social media platforms

## 3. How We Use Your Information

### 3.1 Service Provision
- Create and manage your account
- Authenticate and authorize access to connected social media accounts
- Publish and schedule posts across your social media platforms
- Generate AI-powered content, images, and videos
- Provide analytics and performance insights
- Manage your media library and content organization

### 3.2 Platform Functionality
- Auto-curate content from RSS feeds and news sources
- Send notifications about scheduled posts and account activity
- Provide customer support and respond to inquiries
- Process payments and manage subscriptions
- Enable team collaboration features

### 3.3 Service Improvement
- Analyze usage patterns to improve our platform
- Develop new features and functionality
- Conduct research and analytics
- Optimize performance and user experience
- Prevent fraud and ensure security

### 3.4 Communication
- Send important service announcements
- Provide customer support
- Share product updates and new features
- Send marketing communications (with your consent)

## 4. Information Sharing and Disclosure

### 4.1 Social Media Platforms
We share your content and data with connected social media platforms as necessary to:
- Publish posts and manage your accounts
- Retrieve analytics and performance data
- Facilitate cross-platform functionality
- Comply with platform-specific requirements

### 4.2 Third-Party Service Providers
We share information with trusted third-party service providers who assist us in:
- **AI Services:** OpenAI, Stability AI, and other AI providers for content generation
- **Analytics:** Google Analytics and platform-specific analytics services
- **Payment Processing:** Stripe, PayPal, and other payment processors
- **Cloud Storage:** AWS, Google Cloud, and other cloud service providers
- **Customer Support:** Help desk and communication platforms
- **Media Services:** Unsplash, Pexels, and other stock media providers

### 4.3 Legal Requirements
We may disclose your information if required by law or in response to:
- Court orders, subpoenas, or legal process
- Government requests or investigations
- Protecting our rights, property, or safety
- Preventing fraud or illegal activities
- Enforcing our Terms of Service

### 4.4 Business Transfers
In the event of a merger, acquisition, or sale of assets, your information may be transferred to the new entity, subject to the same privacy protections.

### 4.5 With Your Consent
We may share your information for other purposes with your explicit consent or at your direction.

## 5. Data Security

### 5.1 Security Measures
We implement industry-standard security measures to protect your information:
- Encryption of data in transit and at rest
- Secure authentication and access controls
- Regular security audits and vulnerability assessments
- Secure data centers and infrastructure
- Employee training on data protection

### 5.2 Social Media Tokens
Social media access tokens are:
- Encrypted and stored securely
- Refreshed automatically as needed
- Revoked when you disconnect accounts
- Protected with multi-layer security

### 5.3 Limitations
While we strive to protect your information, no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is 100% secure. We cannot guarantee absolute security.

## 6. Data Retention

### 6.1 Retention Periods
- **Account Information:** Retained while your account is active and for a reasonable period afterward
- **Content Data:** Retained according to your settings and legal requirements
- **Analytics Data:** Aggregated data may be retained indefinitely for service improvement
- **Log Data:** Typically retained for 90 days for security and debugging purposes

### 6.2 Deletion Rights
You can request deletion of your data at any time. Upon account deletion:
- Personal information is removed from our active systems
- Cached or backup data may persist for up to 90 days
- Aggregated, anonymized data may be retained for analytics

## 7. Your Rights and Choices

### 7.1 Access and Control
You have the right to:
- Access your personal information
- Update or correct inaccurate data
- Delete your account and associated data
- Export your data in a portable format
- Restrict or object to certain processing activities

### 7.2 Communication Preferences
You can control communications by:
- Updating your notification settings
- Unsubscribing from marketing emails
- Adjusting in-app notification preferences
- Contacting us directly with preferences

### 7.3 Cookie Management
You can manage cookies through:
- Browser settings and preferences
- Third-party cookie management tools
- Opting out of analytics tracking
- Disabling non-essential cookies

## 8. International Data Transfers

### 8.1 Cross-Border Processing
Your information may be transferred to and processed in countries other than your own, including the United States and other countries where we or our service providers operate.

### 8.2 Safeguards
We ensure appropriate safeguards are in place for international transfers through:
- Standard contractual clauses
- Adequacy decisions by relevant authorities
- Other legally recognized transfer mechanisms

## 9. Children's Privacy

### 9.1 Age Restrictions
Our Service is not intended for children under 13 years of age. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13.

### 9.2 Parental Rights
If you believe we have collected information from a child under 13, please contact us immediately, and we will take steps to remove such information.

## 10. Regional Privacy Rights

### 10.1 European Union (GDPR)
If you are in the EU, you have additional rights under the General Data Protection Regulation:
- Legal basis for processing your data
- Right to data portability
- Right to object to processing
- Right to restrict processing
- Right to lodge a complaint with supervisory authorities

### 10.2 California (CCPA)
California residents have specific rights under the California Consumer Privacy Act:
- Right to know what personal information is collected
- Right to delete personal information
- Right to opt-out of sale of personal information
- Right to non-discrimination for exercising privacy rights

### 10.3 Other Jurisdictions
We comply with applicable privacy laws in all jurisdictions where we operate.

## 11. Third-Party Links and Services

### 11.1 External Links
Our Service may contain links to third-party websites or services. We are not responsible for the privacy practices of these external sites.

### 11.2 Integrated Services
Third-party services integrated into our platform (social media platforms, AI services, analytics tools) have their own privacy policies that govern their use of your information.

## 12. Changes to This Privacy Policy

### 12.1 Updates
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by:
- Posting the new Privacy Policy on this page
- Updating the "Last Updated" date
- Sending email notifications for material changes
- Providing in-app notifications

### 12.2 Continued Use
Your continued use of the Service after any modifications constitutes acceptance of the updated Privacy Policy.

